    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the active buffer is unlisted, `:bn` issues an error refusing to change to existing listed but hidden buffer(s).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n$ `nvim --clean file.txt` # parameters vastly irrelevant\n`:h wtf` # ✔ opens help in split\n`^w^w` # ✔ changes to file.txt window\n`:hid` # ✔ hides file.txt, making help full screen\n`:bn` # ✘ does not change back to file.txt but issues:\n\n> E85: There is no listed buffer\n\n`:ls` # ✔ proves that there is:\n\n>   1  h   \"file.txt\"                     line 2\n\n`:ls!` # ✔ shows the state:\n\n>   1 #h   \"file.txt\"                     line 2\n>   2u%a-  \"luvref.txt\"                   line 4475\n\n`:buf 1` # ✔ changes to file.txt\n`:bn` # ✔ does nothing, shows no error\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:bn` should change to hidden listed buffer (as vim 9.0 does).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3 Build type: Release\nnvim v0.11.0 also was faulty\nnvim v0.10.4 worked well\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.0.2142 works",
