            "body": "OK, thanks for pointing out my inability to read the helpfile and taking an age-old bug for granted.\n\nNevertheless, if you open multiple help buffers and the active window shows one of those, `:bn` still shows\nE85: There is no listed buffer\nSo `:bn` is still broken. But now in a way that it does not act in any desirable way if the active buffer is unlisted (e.g. a help file). The linked bug is not part of the neovim bugtracker and re-opening it would be incorrect, though, right?\n\nAnd I disagree with your statement ‹This is working as intended›.",
