        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`:bnext` still only switches to listed buffers. If there are multiple listed help buffers, you can use `:bnext` is cycle through them. But help buffers are unlisted by default...\n```\n:[N]bn[ext][!] [+cmd] [N]\t\t\t\t*:bn* *:bnext* *E87*\n\t\tGo to [N]th next buffer in buffer list.  [N] defaults to one.\n\t\tWraps around the end of the buffer list.\n```\n```\n\t\t\t\t\t\t*unlisted-buffer*\nunlisted\tThe buffer is not in the buffer list.  It is not used for\n\t\tnormal editing, but to show a help file, remember a file name\n\t\tor marks.  The \":bdelete\" command will also set this option,\n\t\tthus it doesn't completely delete the buffer.  Settings: >\n\t\t\t:setlocal nobuflisted\n```",
